premise_source_doc_sentence: Anschluss  (  -LSB- ˈʔanʃlʊs -RSB- , `` connection '' or `` joining ''  )  is the term used to describe the annexation of Austria into Nazi Germany on 12 March 1938 .

premise_source_doc_sentence: Following the Anschluss of Austria to Nazi Germany , in March 1938 , the conquest of Czechoslovakia became Hitler 's next ambition .

premise_source_doc_sentence: The German occupation of Czechoslovakia  (  1938 -- 1945  )  began with the German annexation of Czechoslovakia 's northern and western border regions , formerly being part of German-Austria known collectively as the Sudetenland , under terms outlined by the Munich Agreement .
